Midgaard's institutional position on the Eccentric Woodland is managed denial: acknowledge it as a
known hazard, maintain pass checks and route advisories to reduce liability, avoid full intervention
because sustained control requires forces diverted from Roc Road and northern forest routes.
Patrol reports since the Lantern Reforms record path drift, contradictory witness accounts, and
landmarks that could not be re-located—filed as routine "variance events." Ledgerhouse records show
persistent mismatch between Southern Wild Gate departures and documented returns. The False Escort
Syndicate consumed significant investigative resources in the last decade without producing
prosecutions. Midgaard refused all three Rakuen annexation petitions citing woodland route instability,
while refusing to fund corridor stabilization that would have made integration feasible—the Southern
Maintenance Paradox the Honest Ledger movement identifies.

